------------------------------------------------------------

EXTRA FEATURES:

The program supports multiple pipes on a single command line,
not only one pipe.

The program also validates pipe syntax and prints an error for
invalid inputs such as:

ls |
| sort

------------------------------------------------------------

KNOWN DEFICIENCIES OR BUGS:

No known bugs at this time.

The program supports only the command formats required by the
assignment. It does not implement shell features such as cd,
background execution, input/output redirection, environment
variable editing, or quoted strings.

------------------------------------------------------------

LESSONS LEARNED:

We learned how a shell reads and processes user commands.

We learned how to create child processes using fork().

We learned how execvp() replaces a child process with another
program.

We learned how pipes allow one process to send output to another
process.

We learned how dup2() redirects standard input and standard output.

We learned the importance of closing unused file descriptors in
pipe-based programs.

We learned how to check system call return values and report errors
using perror().
